<br>
I have several characters over 40th and one over 50th but either they are melees or my neceromancer.  So... big DDs are not something I am familiar with.<br>
<br>
My question is.  When I use my big DD spell... right now that is Shock of Force (173 points of damage) on a mob that resists it.  Why do they agro on me?  Here is what I do in Marus Seru when hunting with my wife.  She is a necro.<br>
<br>
I start with my Lightning Bolt to pull with.  Resisted 90% of the time but has good range.  When its not resisted, her skeleton pet is easily able to get its agro.  When it is resisted... her pet is beating it from behind as it chases me in circles until she darks and fears it.<br>
<br>
If I land my first hit.  Her pet will tank it.  I cast Tishans Clash (I think that is the right spelling) and if it gets resisted... no agro.  YAY!... If it lands... its stunned but no agro.. YAY!<br>
<br>
I follow with Shock of Force when its down to half.  If I land it... Sweet!  It stays on pet.  If its resisted... AGRO!  Running in circles again.  /sigh<br>
<br>
So... Why is it when something resists my spells I get more agro than when they land?<br>
<br>
Thanks... A sorta confused Wizard. <p>Kithmir, High Elven Wizard<br>
